            <br>
			Norrath is changing and Aegis Lux needs to evolve and stay tuned to whats happening.<br><br>Its no secret that true newbies are becoming more rare and the general population of Rodcet Nife has a higher average level than ever before.<br><br>Aegis Lux have numerous members below level 20 who are rarely played. Some are secondary twinks, but others have simply been dropped and the Council spends a lot of time trying to figure out whether or not they are still actively played.<br><br>Now, to meet the rising demands of the ever-evolving Everquest (ye know, the Planes, Kunark, Velious), to cut down the large amount of "inactive characters" , raise the performance of Aegis Lux and imitate the player-base at large, we would like your oppinion on this matter:<br><br><i><b>Should we raise the minimum level you need to be to apply for membership in Aegis Lux?</i></b><br><br>And just to clarify - the current members will naturally NOT be affected by any change in the admission requirements!<br><br><b>So tell us how you feel about this. <br><br>Don't just click on a button - I have made a special post for this on the Private Messageboard. <br><br>Give the Council some feedback.</b><br><br>- Errol
          </td>
